## 5. AI Microservice Technical Specifications

### 5.1 Stack
| Component | Technology | Version |
|---|---|---|
| Language | Python | 3.12 |
| Framework | FastAPI | Latest |
| ML Framework | TensorFlow | 2.21 |
| Base Model | MobileNetV2 | ImageNet pretrained |
| Image Processing | Pillow | Latest |
| ASGI Server | Uvicorn | Latest |

### 5.2 Model Architecture
- **Base:** MobileNetV2 (pretrained on ImageNet, weights frozen)
- **Head:** GlobalAveragePooling2D вҶ’ Dense(128, relu) вҶ’ Dropout(0.5) вҶ’ Dense(38, softmax)
- **Input shape:** (224, 224, 3)
- **Dataset:** PlantVillage вҖ” 54,306 images, 38 disease classes, 14 crops
- **Training:** Transfer learning, ~30 min GPU / ~2-4 hrs CPU
- **Output:** `{predicted_class, confidence, treatment, all_predictions[]}`

### 5.3 API Endpoints
| Method | Path | Description |
|---|---|---|
| GET | `/health` | Returns `{"status":"ok","demo_mode": bool}` |
| POST | `/predict` | Accepts multipart image, returns prediction JSON |

### 5.4 Demo Mode
When `plant_disease_model.h5` is not found, the service returns realistic predictions drawn from `treatments.json` with randomized confidence scores. This allows full frontend testing without a trained model.

### 5.5 Supported Crop/Disease Classes (38 total)
Apple (4), Blueberry (1), Cherry (2), Corn (4), Grape (4), Orange (1), Peach (2), Pepper (2), Potato (3), Raspberry (1), Soybean (1), Squash (1), Strawberry (2), Tomato (10)

